{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the flow direction completely reverses at each maximum and minimum of the oscillation, leading to several zero crossings of the velocity components.",
    "Due to these fluctuations in the velocity magnitude, the relative errors vary significantly with time and increase towards later time steps.",
    "The absolute errors of the inferred fields are distributed more uniformly across the validation dataset, but are locally higher around the extrema of the droplet oscillation.",
    "This is likely caused by the rapid change of the flow topology and velocity magnitude, occurring simultaneously with a low interface motion in the input images, which diminishes the cues for the velocity inference in the spatio-temporal features and leads to a higher uncertainty of the prediction.",
    "However, both relative and absolute errors of the velocity components remain limited, even for very low velocity magnitudes."
  ]
}